## Merging Two Sorted Linked Lists
Given the heads of two sorted lists, we wish to merge them in-place to construct a single sorted linked list output.
* **Algorithm**: We initialize a `dummy` node to act as the root pivot. We compare values of current nodes of both lists and hook the smaller node reference to our pivot tracker.

```javascript
function mergeTwoLists(l1, l2) {
  let dummy = { val: -1, next: null };
  let curr = dummy;

  while (l1 !== null && l2 !== null) {
    if (l1.val <= l2.val) {
      curr.next = l1;
      l1 = l1.next;
    } else {
      curr.next = l2;
      l2 = l2.next;
    }
    curr = curr.next;
  }

  // Attach remaining items
  curr.next = l1 !== null ? l1 : l2;
  return dummy.next;
}
```
